name: Avi Graiver
note: set up a call he is interested in LG

need_candidates.comment_requirements:
Outstaffing Remote Employees
Hire Lead Generators to find new clients. Payment per day, week, month. Can we talk?

Initial Inquiry:
Avi Graiver: Hi, do you have a LinkedIn lead generation expert? What would be the cost per hour?

Response from Mariia Tsykalo:
Hello Avi,
The minimum employment type for a lead generation manager is 40 hours/month, priced at 600 EUR. Would you like me to set up a call on Google Meet to discuss this in more detail?

You may also try the service for one day (8 hours) for 150 EUR.

Follow-up:
Mariia Tsykalo: So, what about the call next week? Are you available?

Further Inquiry:
Avi Graiver: Hi, and what does the service include?

Mariia Tsykalo’s Explanation:
It depends on your needs. A Lead Gen Manager can search for leads (clients), find their contacts, communicate with them, and set up calls with you. They help grow your business by finding more clients for you.

Let’s schedule a Google Meet to discuss your services or needs and how our Lead Gen Managers can assist you. Does that work for you?

Scheduling the Call:
Avi Graiver: Sure, let’s schedule. [Link to a TidyCal meeting page provided by Avi]

Mariia Tsykalo: Is it okay if I set up the call in Google Meet?

Avi Graiver: Sure, no problem.

Mariia Tsykalo: Could you let me know your time zone and preferred time and day? Also, could you share your email address?

Details Provided:
Avi Graiver: I’m in Israel. My email is avi@thecowboy.co.il.

Confirmation of Time:
Mariia Tsykalo: Is tomorrow at 11:30 AM okay for you?

Avi Graiver: I prefer the afternoon.

Mariia Tsykalo: Maybe 3 PM or 4 PM?

Avi Graiver: 3 PM.

Final Confirmation:
Mariia Tsykalo: I’ve set up the call for tomorrow at 3 PM. Please check your email for the invitation or use this link: meet.google.com/thh-vwpm-nuv

client_candidates.comment: Responsibilities: to be skilled in marketing performance, to know simple marketing terms, to understand Google Ads in general, to be able to run ads. English is a must, they expect that our candidate can join their working meetings in the future.

name: Margot Feiner
note: Margot Feiner discussed her innovative business idea with Sales Remote Helpers, aiming to create a sustainable fashion platform where users can rent wardrobe items, targeting environmentally conscious women aged 22-50 across Europe. She has prepared detailed design concepts, competitor analyses, and a gamification feature to ensure trust and engagement. Sales Remote Helpers introduced their business model, offering full-time, dedicated employees to implement Margot’s vision. The next steps involve a follow-up meeting with the assigned developer, Artyom, scheduled for Tuesday, where they will finalize project timelines and expectations.
